docs: the spa / pool area was brilliant - easily deserving of 5 stars - as were the spa staff .we paid extra for a lake view - which it did provide but only if you stood up against the dormer window .big thanks to mrs .otherwise , it´s a great hotel , a beautiful place with incredible magnificient spa .a most amazing breakfast :) . </DOC> i think we will return soon because we just fell in loved with the ambience , the surroundings and the hotel itself .breakfast was excellent ( a review of my evening meal is covered under ' restaurants ' ) .this beautiful hotel in slovakia deserves to be better known - it has great location , beautiful ambience , palatial grandeur , good food & excellent service ! as you enter the driveway up the hill , you see the magnificent stone palace with towers & gables rising up proudly .the grand staircase landing leading up to the first floor has a large painting of colourful flowers , with smaller showcases of jewellery near the foot .behind is the bar and a large sitting area , with a separate smoking room adjoining . </DOC> positives : very professional , printouts provided for suggested hikes , drives , etc welcome drink , good overview of hotel / facilities excellent spa with excellent viewsmy husband and i stayed at this magnificent hotel in order to celebrate my birthday .we could n't have chosen a more perfect place for this .beginning with the welcome glass of champagne while checking in , the entire experience was heavenly .the hotel and our very large room with a view of the lake were beautifully decorated and the spa and pool were elegant and restorative . </DOC> we enjoyed the canoes on the lake , a great massage , the sauna / steam rooms , and especially the footbaths in varying temperatures .my birthday dinner was delicious with lots of local specialties and excellent local wine , and my very own birthday cake provided by the hotel as a surprise .after driving in an extreme fog , slowly ascending from the polish border , the grand hotel towered up in front of us .only downside was to many loud kids in the pool area , but the fault i guess is more the parents that let their off springs roam around .i recommend to visit slovakia by combing the kempinski hotel in bratislava with the kempinski hotel high tatra . </DOC> the drive is 2/3 on newly built highways .the last 12 kms from the highway uphill is one of the most scenic and breathtaking winding roads in the world .then the kempinski shows up next to a few other hotel comlexes and you are in one of the most interesting mountain hotels in the world .i particularly liked the view ( to the valley and to the mountain side ) , the lobby bar and the cigar tent .it was not easy to arrive at this luxury hotel tucked into the high tatra mountains . </DOC> we wanted to travel from budapest to krakow straight through the mountains of slovakia .( in retrospect it would have been worth it to hire a car and driver )instead we took a train from budapest to kosice and another train from kosice to strba --- not as easy as we thought to make the change in kosice very late at night where no one spoke english and we were pronouncing strba incorrectly .however , when we arrived in strba we were met at the station by the kempinski driver who drove us up the mountains to the hotel ..... and to heaven .we woke in the morning and opened the drapes we gasped at the incredible view of the lake and towering mountains . </DOC> the spa is beautiful and free to guests .the kempinski staff online were terrific too .we made our reservations in february for a july stay and wrote lots of emails on the best way to get to the hotel .i received amazing rates - not sure if i could afford it during season .the hotel is in a great location in stbske pleso - in front of the lake with amazing views of the valley . </DOC> it is also close to the ski train so easy access to the slopes .my room was huge and facing the valley with a balcony .the bathroom had underfloor heating which must be fantastic in the winter ( not needed in the spring ) .wonderful location on a magic lake .value for money excellent .
summary: lovely and well maintained , the spa is excellent and the spa is very good .the hotel is located in a quiet area of the city , so you can walk to all the shops and restaurants .it was a great experience and worth the money .the food was excellent and the staff were friendly .there is an excellent restaurant on the premises , but i did n't eat there .</DOC><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad><pad>
